<plot>An older woman faces living alone in her apartment or going into a retirement community. As she looks back over her life she considers choices she's made to please her family and friends. She discovers that acceptable choices shortchanged her happiness and the courage to live her truth would have made her happier The film's enigmatic nature make us wonder whether she has experienced or she is imagining the various relationships she finds herself in: marriage, bi-racial non-commitment, lesbian love, her and her dog walking in the park. What is her choice? Will she choose loneliness, some type of companionship or the retirement community? She has one last opportunity to make her own choice in life.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?104285</url></doc>
